{"id":"elmalg-exprules_quot-002","cid":"ELMALG","topic":"Polynomials and Factoring","subtopic":"Exponent rules","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A scientist writes x^{m} / x^{n} in her formula. Simplify to a single power.","params":{"n":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":8},"extra":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":7}},"answer_expr":"exprules_quot","steps":["Quotient rule: x^m / x^n = x^(m-n). Here m = {m}, n = {n}.","x^{m} / x^{n} = x^{answer_exprules_quot}."],"tags":["elementary-algebra","exponents","quotient-rule"]}
